      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Isolate Claude OAuth usage from CLI refresh",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- prevent Claude OAuth usage fetches in CLI runtime from delegating token refresh through the local Claude CLI\n- skip Claude CLI version detection for OAuth usage, including the OAuth request user agent and post-fetch CLI rendering path\n- preserve app/user-initiated delegated repair for expired Claude-CLI-owned credentials\n- cover CLI/app runtime isolation and platform-specific Keychain prompt policy behavior\n\n## Root Cause\n\nRepeated CLI OAuth polling could still reach two subprocess paths: delegated credential refresh and Claude version detection. On Linux, those subprocesses could launch user-configured MCP tooling and turn a failed usage probe into a crash/coredump loop.\n\n## Compatibility\n\nThe no-delegation and no-version-probe behavior is scoped to CLI OAuth runtime. App OAuth fetches retain delegated refresh and detected-version behavior. Explicit CLI usage and Auto-to-CLI fallback remain available.\n\n## Merge Order\n\nLand after #1799 and #1800; this branch is rebuilt as their clean continuation.\n\n## Validation\n\n- focused OAuth/CLI suites: 82 tests passed\n- `make check`: SwiftFormat and strict SwiftLint clean\n- `make test`: all 44 shards passed\n- bundled autoreview: clean, no actionable findings\n- exact-head Ubuntu 24.04 arm64 build with Swift 6.2.1:\n  - explicit OAuth with an isolated HOME and environment-only fake credential: controlled unauthorized result, exit 3, no Claude sentinel invocation\n  - explicit CLI with a controlled Claude sentinel: parsed usage JSON, exit 0\n  - Auto with the same sentinel: bypassed unsupported web, parsed CLI usage JSON, exit 0\n  - every command completed before its 30-second guard; no exit 139 or core dump\n",
        "branch": "codex/claude-oauth-cli-isolation",
        "head_sha": "3c72adc51e6136a615c99e7e00971c1ddc980ecd",
